Bring a large #pot{} of water to a boil with a large pinch of @salt{}. Trim and discard the bottom inch of the @asparagus{1%bunch}, then cut into 1-inch pieces. Mince the @garlic{2%cloves} and @shallot{1}. Zest and halve @lemon{1}. Chop @mint{1%sprig} leaves.

When boiling, add the @penne pasta{6%ounce} to the water and cook for ~{9-10%minutes}, until al dente. Drain, reserving 1/2 cup pasta water. Set aside. Meanwhile, heat 1 tablespoon @butter{2%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Add the shallot and garlic and cook for ~{2-3%minutes}, until soft and fragrant. Add the asparagus to the pan and cook, tossing, ~{2-3%minutes} more, until bright green and crisp-tender. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the @peas{4%ounce} to the pan and cook for ~{1%minute} more, until heated through. Add another 1 tablespoon butter, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, a splash of pasta water, chopped mint, and a squeeze of lemon. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add drained pasta to the pan and cook over medium heat, tossing for ~{1%minute}. Stir in the @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} and add a splash of remaining pasta water, if needed, to thin out the sauce. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Serve the pasta divided between bowls with a generous dollop of @ricotta{1%cup}. Top ricotta with a drizzle of @olive oil{1} and sprinkling @salt{} and @pepper{}. Sprinkle the pasta with lemon zest and enjoy.

> Spring is in the air! We're looking forward to warmer months with classic early-Spring ingredients like asparagus, mint and sweet peas! A dollop of creamy ricotta with a drizzle of olive oil is a luscious way to finish off this light and bright pasta.